  "_doc": [
    "Manual club-name alias table for THE DRAW Career Path identity resolution (Ticket E0).",
    "",
    "WHY THIS EXISTS: identity gating matches a Career Path club name against a Wikidata club",
    "entity's label + skos:altLabel set, using STRICT normalized equality (accent-folded,",
    "lowercased, punctuation->space). Strict equality is deliberate: the tempting alternative -",
    "stripping affix tokens like FC/AC/CF - collapses 'AC Milan' to {milan}, which then collides",
    "with other Milan clubs. Wikidata's own altLabels already cover most variants ('Manchester",
    "United' IS an alias of Q18656; 'Real Madrid' IS an alias of Q8682), so this table only holds",
    "the residue: clubs whose common bare name is NOT among their Wikidata aliases.",
    "",
    "SEMANTICS: aliases[careerPathClubName] = additional Wikidata names that also count as a match",
    "for that club name. Matching is directional and additive - the Career Path name itself is",
    "always an accepted name. Entries here only ever ADD possible matches; they never force one.",
    "",
    "SAFETY: keep entries specific. Never add a bare city/nickname that several clubs share",
    "(e.g. do NOT map 'Milan' -> 'Inter Milan'). A wrong entry here can defeat the identity gate.",
    "",
    "MAINTENANCE: `cp-report` prints the club names that most often failed to match a candidate's",
    "P54 set ('unmatched club names'). That list is the queue for extending this table, but it",
    "CONFLATES two causes: (a) a real alias gap, where Wikidata knows the club under another name",
    "(Career Path 'Nice' vs label 'OGC Nice') - fixable here; and (b) Wikidata simply not recording",
    "that club membership on the player at all (e.g. 'Málaga', which already matches exactly yet",
    "still appears in the queue) - NOT fixable here. Before adding an entry, confirm the club exists",
    "in the fetched club dictionary under a different name; if it does not, the alias table cannot",
    "help and the gap is upstream.",
    "",
    "Entries below were derived from labels observed in the fetched club dictionary, not recalled",
    "from memory. Ambiguous bare names were deliberately SKIPPED: 'Al-Ahli' matches three distinct",
    "clubs (Shabab AlAhli Dubai / Al Ahli FC / Al Ahli SC), so mapping it would risk a false match."
  ],
